Package com.zendesk.sdk.network.impl

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ZendeskRequestService.RequestLoadingListener
    This interface allows you to subscribe to the events that occur in the lifecycle of displaying the list of Request in the RequestListFragment
    ZendeskRequestService.SubmissionListener
    This interface allows you to subscribe to the lifecycle events that take place during the submission of a resource like Comments or Requests
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConfigurationIntentService
    This service will periodically request updated SdkSettings from your Zendesk server.
    ZendeskCallback<T>
    This abstract class is used to define success and error callbacks that are used in API calls.
    ZendeskHelpCenterProvider
    Provider used to retrieve data from a Help Center instance.
    ZendeskHelpCenterService
    Service to provide GET operations for Help Center objects by wrapping the HelpCenterService

    ZendeskPicassoProvider
    This will be an instance of picasso that we can use for downloading attachments from our servers.
    ZendeskRequestProvider
    Provider used to retrieve Request from a Zendesk instance.
    ZendeskRequestService
    Service to provide CRUD operations for Requests by wrapping the RequestService

    ZendeskSdkSettingsProvider
    This provider will allow you to download SdkSettings from your Zendesk.
    ZendeskSdkSettingsService
    This is a concrete class that wraps the SdkSettingsService which is used to retrieve Settings from your Zendesk instance.
    ZendeskService
    Abstract class for all Zendesk services that use Retrofit as a transport layer.
    ZendeskUploadProvider
    Provider used to upload files to a Zendesk instance and retrieve UploadResponse
    ZendeskUploadService
    Service to provide POST operations for uploading/deleting files UploadService
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ZendeskConfig
    Configuration class for Zendesk initialization.
    ZendeskGsonProvider
    This class' purpose is to provide a Gson instance that is compliant with how we serialise and deserialise our models.
